hammer.api

Interface Injector


  • public interface Injector
    An Injector is a JSR-330 compliant dependency injection tool. Injectors support all standard JSR-330 dependency injection techniques.

      • getInstance

        <T> T getInstance(Class<T> target)
        Retrieve an instance of the target type from the container. This method may create a new instance or return an existing instance of the requested type depending on the configured Scope of the type as well as the contextual active Scopes of this Injector instance.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the returned object
        Parameters:
        target - the target class type of the returned object
        Returns:
        a fully instantiated instance of the requested type with all configured dependencies injected according to the rules of JSR-330 annotations

      • getActiveScopes

        Set<Annotation> getActiveScopes()
        The set of @Scopes that this Injector instance honors. For every @Scope annotation in this set, all injections by this Injector for a type with said annotation will have one of two behaviors:
        1. If the Scope annotation is also annotated with Multiton, all injections by this injector for a type annotated will return a unique instance per Qualifier annotation associated with the injection request. Thus two requests for the type with the same Qualifier will inject the same instance, but two requests for the type with different Qualifiers will return different instances.
        2. If the Scope annotation is NOT also annotated with Multiton, all injections by this injector for a type annotated with the scope will inject the same instance (behaves as a @Singleton).
        As a rule, this method always returns a set of at least size two where @Singleton and Multiton are always included.
        Returns:
        the Scopes active for this Injector

      • injectMembers

        void injectMembers(Object target)
        Injects injectable member fields and methods of the given object according to the injection rules as specified by the JSR-330 specification. This method will always override any existing value for any injectable member field. This method will also always call every injectable method on the given target object with the appropriate parameters. This method will be called automatically for any instance created by this Injector if member InjectionTypes are configured. Thus in most cases, it is only necessary to use for objects that you instantiate yourself.

        Note: If this Injector is not configured for either public or non public member InjectionTypes, this method will silently have no effect.

        Parameters:
        target - the object to inject
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the target object is of a type unknown to the injector

      • injectStatics

        void injectStatics(Class<?> targetClass)
        Injects injectable static fields and methods of the given class according to the injection rules as specified by the JSR-330 specification. This method will always override any existing value for any injectable static field. This method will also always call every injectable method on the given target object with the appropriate parameters. This method will be called automatically for any class that had static injections requested during Injector creation time if static field InjectionTypes are configured. Thus in most cases, it is only necessary to use for objects that you instantiate yourself.

        Note: If this Injector is not configured for either public or non public static InjectionTypes, this method will silently have no effect.

        Parameters:
        targetClass - the class type to inject
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the target object is of a type unknown to the injector

      • isSupported

        boolean isSupported(InjectionType type)
        Indicates whether or not the given injection type is supported by this Injector instance.
        Parameters:
        type - the type of injection
        Returns:
        true if this Injector supports the given injection type

      • enterScope

        Injector enterScope(Class<? extends Annotation> scope)
        Create a new child Injector with the given scope activated. The resulting child Injector will delegate all injection requests to the parent injector with the exception of requests with the given scope.
        Parameters:
        scope - the new scope to activate in the new Injector
        Returns:
        a new Injector with the given scope activated
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the requested scope annotation is not annotated with @Scope
